Hello, I'm tinsnip.

Feeling rather ineffable these days. Expect a great deal of Good Omens.

Other interests: Star Trek. (Primarily DS9 and Cardassians.)
Pratchett. Wodehouse.
Cats. The Doctors Whom. Science. Cute things. Life truths. Pixels. And spiders, sometimes, so keep that in mind.

summary: Look, listen, I just can’t, I can’t afford to fall in love with Tennant as Crowley. I’m already head over heels gonzo for Sheen...
body:
Look, listen, I just can’t, I can’t afford to fall in love with Tennant as Crowley. I’m already head over heels gonzo for Sheen as Aziraphale.

It’s just that I’ve managed to avoid the mad love for Tennant that pervades this website. I started watching Doctor Who and he’s not my favourite, for God’s sake, and I’ve had a perverse little pride in that, and now–

Now–

He’s so good as the character and apparently he’s a really nice person and I just can’t–

It’s a matter of pride!

summary:
PHOTOS: David Tennant At Good Omens Screening And Panel In LA 

David Tennant attended a special event for Good Omens in LA on...
caption:
PHOTOS: David Tennant At Good Omens Screening And Panel In LA

David Tennant attended a special event for Good Omens in LA on Wednesday where he joined his co stars Michael McKean (Witchfinder Sergeant Shadwell) and the series director Douglas Mackinnon at a screening on Sunset Boulevard.
The Amazon Prime event consisted of a screening and a Q&A panel hosted by Aisha Tyler and was followed by a reception. The event was only open to Television Academy National Active Members.

Good Omens is a dark, comedic story set in modern day Britain on the brink of the Apocalypse. When a fussy angel, Aziraphale (Michael Sheen) and a suave demon, Crowley (David Tennant) get wind of the coming of the Antichrist, they join forces to prevent the loss of their comfortable lifestyle on Earth. Throw in a medley of unforgettable characters, some infernal riders, a host of angels, a legion of demons and a gang of unruly kids, and the end of the world will never be funnier! The show also stars Michael McKean, Jack Whitehall, Adria Arjona, Mireille Enos, Nick Offerman and Nina Sosanya. It will be released worldwide on Amazon Prime on 31st May.
